# Project Structure & Flow

This repository is `gh-pr-rev-md`, a Python CLI that fetches GitHub pull request review comments and formats them as Markdown.

- Entry point CLI: [gh_pr_rev_md/cli.py](mdc:gh_pr_rev_md/cli.py)
- GitHub API client: [gh_pr_rev_md/github_client.py](mdc:gh_pr_rev_md/github_client.py)
- Markdown formatter: [gh_pr_rev_md/formatter.py](mdc:gh_pr_rev_md/formatter.py)
- Config helpers: [gh_pr_rev_md/config.py](mdc:gh_pr_rev_md/config.py)

High-level flow:
1. CLI parses PR URL and options
2. GitHub client fetches review comments (paginated)
3. Formatter renders Markdown
4. Output goes to stdout or a file

When navigating code or adding features, start from the CLI and trace into the client and formatter.

